97
00:06:43.611 --> 00:06:45.839
You don't need to already worry about that.

98
00:06:45.863 --> 00:06:49.483
You never know what will happen in life.

99
00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:52.194
But as you know,

100
00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:56.406
my son isn't well, so I wonder if he'll manage.

101
00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:58.477
In that case,

102
00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:02.272
you should hire a trustworthy farm manager.

103
00:07:02.296 --> 00:07:05.609
And I can help him with
medicines and vaccinations,

104
00:07:05.633 --> 00:07:08.126
so don't worry about that.

105
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:09.822
Thank you so much.

106
00:07:09.846 --> 00:07:11.698
- Thank you.
- Goodness.

107
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:12.950
I'm counting on you.

108
00:07:12.974 --> 00:07:15.869
Why are you suddenly acting like this?

109
00:07:15.893 --> 00:07:19.039
I haven't even retired yet.

110
00:07:19.063 --> 00:07:20.958
<i>My mom is acting weird.</i>

111
00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:23.085
All moms are weird.

112
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.420
They're always getting angry.

113
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:26.547
That's because you bought...

114
00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:30.566
$200 worth of items for a game on her phone.

115
00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:34.194
Kids can sometimes make mistakes.

116
00:07:35.746 --> 00:07:37.516
What about Ms. Jin?

117
00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:39.408
How is she weird?

118
00:07:41.169 --> 00:07:44.621
Hey! How is she weird?

119
00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:47.291
Don't you hear me?

120
00:07:48.384 --> 00:07:50.446
Gosh, this is so frustrating.

121
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.546
Goodness.

122
00:07:54.182 --> 00:07:55.325
You can't do this.

123
00:07:55.349 --> 00:07:57.411
Mi-joo doesn't like us hanging out.

124
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:59.288
How is this hanging out?

125
00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:00.831
We just met by chance.

126
00:08:00.855 --> 00:08:02.681
Isn't that right?

127
00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:07.463
It happens pretty often in
a tiny village like this one.

128
00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:08.422
But...

129
00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:10.466
Don't worry.

130
00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:12.759
Mom went into town.

131
00:08:12.783 --> 00:08:13.886
Town?

132
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:15.804
When? Did she take her wallet?

133
00:08:15.828 --> 00:08:17.347
That's not what's important.

134
00:08:17.371 --> 00:08:20.240
So how is Ms. Jin weird?

135
00:08:22.835 --> 00:08:24.938
She doesn't talk as much.

136
00:08:24.962 --> 00:08:27.065
She doesn't talk as much?

137
00:08:27.089 --> 00:08:31.528
Shouldn't you be glad then?
She won't nag you as much.

138
00:08:31.552 --> 00:08:34.630
She's low on energy and doesn't smile anymore.

139
00:08:35.306 --> 00:08:36.492
Kang-ho!

140
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:38.368
Kang-ho!

141
00:08:38.392 --> 00:08:42.289
Kang-ho, there you are. I've
been looking everywhere for you.

142
00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:45.250
Hi, Ye-jin and Seo-jin. You're here too.

143
00:08:45.274 --> 00:08:46.251
What's this?

144
00:08:46.275 --> 00:08:47.794
Your new toy?

145
00:08:47.818 --> 00:08:50.839
Good for you. It must be from your mom.

146
00:08:50.863 --> 00:08:54.009
Is your grandma well too?
Please say hi to her for me.

147
00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:57.471
Uncle Kang-ho has an appointment.
We'll be going now.

148
00:08:57.495 --> 00:09:00.322
All right, let's go!

149
00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:07.496
Didn't he say she's not talking as much?

150
00:09:10.299 --> 00:09:11.276
You're back.

151
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:12.611
You said you'd return.

152
00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.655
I didn't sell these just in case.

153
00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.907
I'm actually looking for boots today.

154
00:09:16.931 --> 00:09:18.283
Not those?

155
00:09:18.307 --> 00:09:20.994
These are a bit short.

156
00:09:21.018 --> 00:09:22.329
Is there anything higher?

157
00:09:22.353 --> 00:09:24.498
I have ones that go to the waist. One second.

158
00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:26.848
They don't need to be that high.

159
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:29.610
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Women's Shoes $15
Dress Shoes $15</font></i>

160
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.217
It's Tiger.

161
00:09:35.241 --> 00:09:36.718
Tiger.

162
00:09:36.742 --> 00:09:38.568
Tiger!

163
00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:41.947
Tiger.

164
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:44.366
Uri!

165
00:09:48.045 --> 00:09:49.106
Excuse me.

166
00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:51.358
Isn't this Tiger?

167
00:09:51.382 --> 00:09:52.401
What?

168
00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:54.084
Tiger?

169
00:09:55.219 --> 00:09:58.740
It looked just like Tiger,
so I thought it was him.

170
00:09:58.764 --> 00:10:01.091
- Hi.
- What's with him?

171
00:10:03.227 --> 00:10:05.762
Goodness, it's all right.

172
00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:11.351
Where did he go?

173
00:10:11.527 --> 00:10:13.005
Kang-ho...

174
00:10:13.029 --> 00:10:14.646
Kang-ho.

175
00:10:15.489 --> 00:10:16.466
Kang-ho!

176
00:10:16.490 --> 00:10:19.192
- Not bad, right?
- Are you selling it?

177
00:10:19.452 --> 00:10:21.528
I barely managed to get it.

178
00:10:23.914 --> 00:10:26.199
This was the last pack.

179
00:10:28.085 --> 00:10:29.619
It's in here.

180
00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:33.233
No, I put it in here.

181
00:10:33.257 --> 00:10:34.791
There it is.

182
00:10:35.217 --> 00:10:37.502
You punks.

183
00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:38.822
What the heck?

184
00:10:38.846 --> 00:10:41.006
You're too young to smoke.

185
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:43.967
Here.

186
00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:48.138
Don't smoke, okay?

187
00:10:51.984 --> 00:10:54.019
Hey, wait.

188
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:56.897
I gave you $50.

189
00:10:57.907 --> 00:11:00.067
You gave me $5.

190
00:11:00.242 --> 00:11:03.013
That's a bunch of bull.
I definitely gave you $50.

191
00:11:03.037 --> 00:11:04.097
That's a bunch of bull.

192
00:11:04.121 --> 00:11:06.183
Give him back his money, you idiot.

193
00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:07.824
- Seriously.
- Darn it.

194
00:11:07.875 --> 00:11:09.019
I'm not an idiot.

195
00:11:09.043 --> 00:11:10.896
I just went back to my childhood.

196
00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:13.205
This is a chance given from above.

197
00:11:14.715 --> 00:11:17.069
That's one heck of a stupid chance.

198
00:11:17.093 --> 00:11:18.904
You're not going to give me my money?

199
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:20.197
You leave us no choice then.

200
00:11:20.221 --> 00:11:21.698
- Search him.
- No, stop it.

201
00:11:21.722 --> 00:11:23.241
- Pull them down.
- Come on.

202
00:11:23.265 --> 00:11:24.242
You're dead.

203
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:25.577
I'm telling my mom.

204
00:11:25.601 --> 00:11:27.079
Wait, is that a gift?

205
00:11:27.103 --> 00:11:28.455
Give it to me.

206
00:11:28.479 --> 00:11:30.088
It's not a gift. It's a phone, idiot.

207
00:11:30.112 --> 00:11:31.875
I know that, idiot.

208
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:34.851
- You're the idiot, idiot.
- Give it to me, you...!

209
00:11:36.070 --> 00:11:37.547
You rotten jerks!

210
00:11:37.571 --> 00:11:40.148
- What the...?
- Darn it.

211
00:11:40.449 --> 00:11:41.760
Hey, run!

212
00:11:41.784 --> 00:11:42.761
You...!

213
00:11:42.785 --> 00:11:44.930
- Run!
- Stop right there!

214
00:11:44.954 --> 00:11:46.780
You douchebag!

215
00:11:47.706 --> 00:11:50.033
You douchebag!

216
00:11:50.459 --> 00:11:52.536
Repeat after me!

217
00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:54.913
You douchebag.

218
00:11:55.631 --> 00:11:57.859
You douchebag.

219
00:11:57.883 --> 00:11:59.668
Louder!

220
00:12:00.594 --> 00:12:01.947
You douchebag!

221
00:12:01.971 --> 00:12:02.948
That's it.

222
00:12:02.972 --> 00:12:04.658
Good.

223
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:08.370
If anyone calls you an idiot or a cripple,

224
00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:11.847
tell them, "You douchebag!" Got it?

225
00:12:12.106 --> 00:12:14.683
- But I'm not allowed to...
- You are!

226
00:12:23.534 --> 00:12:24.886
Here.

227
00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:28.265
These are all yours now.

228
00:12:28.289 --> 00:12:29.266
Mine?

229
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:31.685
These are all very important,

230
00:12:31.709 --> 00:12:34.744
so don't show them to anyone, okay?

231
00:12:34.795 --> 00:12:37.858
"Kang-ho, let's exchange this for that."

232
00:12:37.882 --> 00:12:39.651
"Kang-ho, stamp your seal here."

233
00:12:39.675 --> 00:12:42.404
"Kang-ho, can you stand surety for me?"

234
00:12:42.428 --> 00:12:44.614
"Kang-ho, let me borrow your house deed."

235
00:12:44.638 --> 00:12:46.464
What do you say then?

236
00:12:47.183 --> 00:12:50.093
- What should you say?
- You douchebag!

237
00:12:50.186 --> 00:12:51.845
Good.

238
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.722
Very good.

239
00:12:55.274 --> 00:12:56.933
Also,

240
00:12:57.401 --> 00:13:01.756
this is a bank account your dad set up for you,

241
00:13:01.780 --> 00:13:05.510
and I've been saving up to
give to you when you get married.

242
00:13:05.534 --> 00:13:07.804
This is very important,

243
00:13:07.828 --> 00:13:10.599
so I'll hide it here.

244
00:13:10.623 --> 00:13:13.268
Don't tell or show anybody, okay?

245
00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:14.603
Okay.

246
00:13:14.627 --> 00:13:16.396
Like my lunch money.

247
00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:17.314
What?

248
00:13:17.338 --> 00:13:19.608
You hid it in my bag.

249
00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:22.068
"Don't lose your lunch money."

250
00:13:22.092 --> 00:13:25.071
This is your lunch money.

251
00:13:25.095 --> 00:13:27.616
You could lose it or get it stolen,

252
00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:30.202
so keep it safe until you
give it to your teacher.

253
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:31.843
Okay.

254
00:13:37.566 --> 00:13:39.184
Yes, you're right.

255
00:13:39.443 --> 00:13:41.963
I hid it in the bottom of your bag, right?

256
00:13:41.987 --> 00:13:43.632
Yes.

257
00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:45.982
What a smart boy.

258
00:13:46.408 --> 00:13:47.969
Yes.

259
00:13:47.993 --> 00:13:49.971
You're doing well.

260
00:13:49.995 --> 00:13:53.433
You can slowly regain your memory
and learn one thing at a time.

261
00:13:53.457 --> 00:13:56.243
- Okay?
- Okay.

262
00:13:58.087 --> 00:14:00.148
You must be hungry.

263
00:14:00.172 --> 00:14:01.191
Let's eat.

264
00:14:01.215 --> 00:14:02.916
Okay.

265
00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:07.030
Aren't we going to eat?

266
00:14:07.054 --> 00:14:08.323
We will.

267
00:14:08.347 --> 00:14:12.717
But if we want to eat, we need rice.

268
00:14:12.768 --> 00:14:17.013
To buy rice, we need money.
And for money, we raise pigs.

269
00:14:17.731 --> 00:14:20.934
And now I'll teach you how to do that.

270
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:26.299
Twice a day, morning and night.

271
00:14:26.323 --> 00:14:28.552
When you're hungry,

272
00:14:28.576 --> 00:14:31.486
come to the farm before you eat,

273
00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:35.031
and check if the pigs are eating well.

274
00:14:35.916 --> 00:14:37.143
If the feed gets wet...

275
00:14:37.167 --> 00:14:39.229
or freezes in cold weather,

276
00:14:39.253 --> 00:14:41.147
it clumps and clogs the feed tube.

277
00:14:41.171 --> 00:14:43.525
When that happens,

278
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:45.527
tap here a few times.

279
00:14:45.551 --> 00:14:47.904
Bang, bang, bang.

280
00:14:47.928 --> 00:14:50.907
You must always keep it neat and disinfected...

281
00:14:50.931 --> 00:14:54.634
so our pigs don't get sick, okay?

282
00:14:55.477 --> 00:14:57.596
Make sure...

283
00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.791
the pigs are happy at our farm.

284
00:14:59.815 --> 00:15:02.726
Yes, Happy Farm.

285
00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:06.464
You can take pig manure...

286
00:15:06.488 --> 00:15:09.065
and use it as fertilizer for the potato field.

287
00:15:09.533 --> 00:15:11.484
Okay.

288
00:15:13.871 --> 00:15:16.224
First spread the manure over the field,

289
00:15:16.248 --> 00:15:19.978
then cover it with plastic to
block weeds from growing.

290
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:20.937
And then...

291
00:15:20.961 --> 00:15:23.899
make holes in the plastic
to plant seed potatoes.

292
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:25.457
Like this.

293
00:15:44.735 --> 00:15:46.728
Nice shot.

294
00:15:48.155 --> 00:15:51.066
Choi Kang-ho! Focus.

295
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:58.433
When the humidity reads over 60,
it means it's too humid.

296
00:15:58.457 --> 00:16:00.158
Use this app...

297
00:16:00.501 --> 00:16:02.911
to turn the fans on.

298
00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:07.499
If the pigs...

299
00:16:07.591 --> 00:16:10.362
develop a cough, get diarrhea,

300
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:12.280
or collapse for no reason...

301
00:16:12.304 --> 00:16:15.367
"Hello, I'm calling from Happy Farm in Jou-ri."

302
00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:17.911
"My pigs are coughing or having diarrhea,"

303
00:16:17.935 --> 00:16:19.913
"so please come quickly."

304
00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:24.099
But if the vet can't come because
of an outbreak of infectious disease?

305
00:16:25.067 --> 00:16:29.896
Then you need to buy the
medicine yourself and inject them.

306
00:16:30.614 --> 00:16:33.983
If you don't, the contagion will spread.

307
00:16:34.284 --> 00:16:36.471
I don't want to. Shots are scary.

308
00:16:36.495 --> 00:16:38.306
- I can't do this.
- No.

309
00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:39.766
It's easy.

310
00:16:39.790 --> 00:16:42.659
Just stab it like this.

311
00:16:45.879 --> 00:16:48.748
Mom, you're the best. That's so cool.

312
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:53.071
When mother pigs have piglets,

313
00:16:53.095 --> 00:16:56.047
she feeds and licks them.

314
00:16:56.515 --> 00:17:00.370
She teaches them everything,
where to eat and poop,

315
00:17:00.394 --> 00:17:02.664
how to scratch an itch,

316
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:06.266
and how to grunt when they're angry.

317
00:17:07.067 --> 00:17:12.397
Then after 25 nights, you wean them.

318
00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:15.468
I'd like the newly-released knit gel polishes,

319
00:17:15.492 --> 00:17:17.470
a set of semicircular pearls in all sizes,

320
00:17:17.494 --> 00:17:19.264
and a box of nail tinctures.

321
00:17:19.288 --> 00:17:22.559
And ten bottles of moisturizing cream too.

322
00:17:22.583 --> 00:17:23.727
Yes.

323
00:17:23.751 --> 00:17:28.398
Tomorrow's the grand opening,
so I need them by 9 a.m.

324
00:17:28.422 --> 00:17:30.608
Yes, okay. That'd be great.

325
00:17:30.632 --> 00:17:32.834
Thank you. Bye.

326
00:17:36.180 --> 00:17:39.090
The charms came off.

327
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:43.496
You're going to open a nail salon
in the agricultural chemicals shop?

328
00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:44.497
Yes.

329
00:17:44.521 --> 00:17:45.957
The rent is cheap,

330
00:17:45.981 --> 00:17:49.294
and there's lots of foot traffic,
so I think it'll be great.

331
00:17:49.318 --> 00:17:50.754
That's not a bad idea.

332
00:17:50.778 --> 00:17:55.774
People may buy pesticides
to take their own life,

333
00:17:55.824 --> 00:17:59.596
then get their nails done and feel better.

334
00:17:59.620 --> 00:18:01.973
What if they get their nails done...

335
00:18:01.997 --> 00:18:05.366
and see pesticides and
want to take their own life?

336
00:18:08.545 --> 00:18:11.664
I was just joking. Don't mind me.

337
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:15.237
A nail salon in a shop that
sells agricultural chemicals.

338
00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:17.171
That's kind of novel.

339
00:18:18.680 --> 00:18:20.950
So don't come here...

340
00:18:20.974 --> 00:18:23.745
and ask her to do this for free anymore.

341
00:18:23.769 --> 00:18:25.804
Go to her nail salon.

342
00:18:27.356 --> 00:18:29.751
Where is Sung-ae?

343
00:18:29.775 --> 00:18:32.754
She left in a hurry to go to the bank.

344
00:18:32.778 --> 00:18:34.380
The bank?

345
00:18:34.404 --> 00:18:35.757
Wait.

346
00:18:35.781 --> 00:18:39.400
Is she borrowing money to
settle Sam-sik's trouble again?

347
00:18:40.410 --> 00:18:45.391
♫ <i>It's time for us to say goodbye</i> ♫

348
00:18:45.415 --> 00:18:48.186
♫ <i>until we meet again</i> ♫

349
00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:49.896
Get $100,000 ready.

350
00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:52.065
If you fail to do that,

351
00:18:52.089 --> 00:18:54.958
you'll end up...

352
00:18:57.261 --> 00:18:58.613
donating your organs...

353
00:18:58.637 --> 00:19:00.657
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Waiver of Physical Rights</font></i>

354
00:19:00.681 --> 00:19:03.216
...to many who are about to die.

355
00:19:03.267 --> 00:19:04.884
Okay?

356
00:19:19.116 --> 00:19:20.909
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Mi-joo</font></i>

357
00:19:22.786 --> 00:19:24.445
Hello...

358
00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:26.155
Honey?

359
00:19:26.206 --> 00:19:27.433
Where are you?

360
00:19:27.457 --> 00:19:29.269
<i>What do you mean, where am I?</i>

361
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:31.187
<i>I'm obviously out in the Pacific.</i>

362
00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:32.730
Right?

363
00:19:32.754 --> 00:19:35.233
You haven't returned and
gotten in trouble, have you?

364
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:37.902
Don't say that to someone
who's turned over a fresh leaf...

365
00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:40.503
and working hard catching fish.

366
00:19:41.930 --> 00:19:43.074
Hey, Mr. Kim!

367
00:19:43.098 --> 00:19:46.050
<i>Can you pull on the nets?</i>

368
00:19:46.894 --> 00:19:49.122
<i>I'm practically made for this job.</i>

369
00:19:49.146 --> 00:19:53.099
I even caught a mermaid yesterday.

370
00:19:53.525 --> 00:19:55.378
<i>Where are you?</i>

371
00:19:55.402 --> 00:19:57.881
You aren't drinking alone
after getting fired, right?

372
00:19:57.905 --> 00:19:59.257
<i>Fired?</i>

373
00:19:59.281 --> 00:20:01.551
I'm opening up my own nail salon.

374
00:20:01.575 --> 00:20:03.803
I finished decorating the place today.

375
00:20:03.827 --> 00:20:05.138
<i>Really?</i>

376
00:20:05.162 --> 00:20:07.765
I knew it, Mi-joo.

377
00:20:07.789 --> 00:20:10.867
You got back on your
feet after that tough ordeal.

378
00:20:11.752 --> 00:20:15.857
I felt really bad when you
said you wanted to give up...

379
00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:18.291
and go back to our hometown.

380
00:20:18.592 --> 00:20:21.279
<i>You're too talented to lurk in the countryside.</i>

381
00:20:21.303 --> 00:20:24.005
You should do nails for rich ladies in...

382
00:20:25.724 --> 00:20:28.286
Hello?

383
00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:31.539
Let me call you back.

384
00:20:31.563 --> 00:20:33.556
Okay, sure.

385
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:36.142
What was that?

386
00:20:39.404 --> 00:20:41.606
Lee Mi-joo?

387
00:20:41.949 --> 00:20:43.775
Wait.

388
00:20:45.911 --> 00:20:48.097
Sam-sik!

389
00:20:48.121 --> 00:20:49.891
Hey, Bang Sam-sik!

390
00:20:49.915 --> 00:20:51.517
Is that you?

391
00:20:51.541 --> 00:20:54.187
When did you get back?

392
00:20:54.211 --> 00:20:56.731
When did you come back?

393
00:20:56.755 --> 00:21:00.568
You said you'd surprise me when we met again,

394
00:21:00.592 --> 00:21:02.418
and you were right.

395
00:21:04.096 --> 00:21:06.965
Were you beaten up by the mermaid you caught?

396
00:21:08.058 --> 00:21:10.828
You see, out there in the Pacific,

397
00:21:10.852 --> 00:21:14.639
there's a world of men you don't know about.

398
00:21:15.983 --> 00:21:17.835
- Gosh.
- What do you know...

399
00:21:17.859 --> 00:21:20.046
♫ <i>about a man's heart</i> ♫

400
00:21:20.070 --> 00:21:22.465
- What's with you?
- Sorry.

401
00:21:22.489 --> 00:21:23.800
You must be insane.

402
00:21:23.824 --> 00:21:29.320
What about you? You're doing nails
for country ladies, not rich ladies?

403
00:21:30.163 --> 00:21:31.557
What do you know...

404
00:21:31.581 --> 00:21:34.158
♫ <i>about a woman's heart</i> ♫

405
00:21:35.836 --> 00:21:37.954
What are you doing?

406
00:21:39.715 --> 00:21:41.416
Right.

407
00:21:41.550 --> 00:21:42.986
Since we both ended up here,

408
00:21:43.010 --> 00:21:46.322
let's try not to judge each other.

409
00:21:46.346 --> 00:21:48.825
Who are we to criticize one another?

410
00:21:48.849 --> 00:21:51.551
We both messed up.

411
00:21:53.145 --> 00:21:56.499
But still, we're better off than Kang-ho.

412
00:21:56.523 --> 00:21:59.002
He used to be so haughty
like he owned the world.

413
00:21:59.026 --> 00:22:00.586
Did you see? He became an idiot.

414
00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:02.964
- Hey!
- Goodness, you startled me.

415
00:22:02.988 --> 00:22:07.427
How could you say such a thing
about someone who's unwell?

416
00:22:07.451 --> 00:22:11.237
The anger is bringing out your dialect.

417
00:22:11.288 --> 00:22:14.350
That's my Mi-joo. You're so cute, as always.

418
00:22:14.374 --> 00:22:16.227
Gosh, you idiot.

419
00:22:16.251 --> 00:22:18.938
All right.

420
00:22:18.962 --> 00:22:20.523
I'm sorry.

421
00:22:20.547 --> 00:22:23.791
You didn't have to get so worked up.

422
00:22:24.509 --> 00:22:25.737
Hold on.

423
00:22:25.761 --> 00:22:30.465
Do you still like Kang-ho?

424
00:22:30.974 --> 00:22:32.493
- You're insane.
- Do you?

425
00:22:32.517 --> 00:22:34.510
Gosh, move!

426
00:22:35.062 --> 00:22:38.416
You're suddenly dodging my question.

427
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.043
You do.

428
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:41.642
You still do.

429
00:22:42.402 --> 00:22:43.880
People avoid poop...

430
00:22:43.904 --> 00:22:46.257
not because it's dirty,

431
00:22:46.281 --> 00:22:48.316
but because it's scary.

432
00:22:53.955 --> 00:22:55.850
You're scared of poop?

433
00:22:55.874 --> 00:22:57.643
Mi-joo, why?

434
00:22:57.667 --> 00:23:00.161
Why are you scared of it?

435
00:23:09.012 --> 00:23:10.573
Seo-jin, what's wrong?

436
00:23:10.597 --> 00:23:12.283
What is it? Why are you crying?

437
00:23:12.307 --> 00:23:13.785
Did you hit him again?

438
00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:15.870
- Come here.
- I didn't hit him.

439
00:23:15.894 --> 00:23:19.457
He's crying because he doesn't
want to go to the public bath.

440
00:23:19.481 --> 00:23:22.141
- What?
- Mom.

441
00:23:22.484 --> 00:23:26.047
Do I have to go to the public bath?

442
00:23:26.071 --> 00:23:30.843
I really hate going to the women's bath...

443
00:23:30.867 --> 00:23:33.861
with Grandma and Ye-jin.

444
00:23:36.039 --> 00:23:41.577
Last week, he ran into Yun-ji
and Da-hyeon from kindergarten.

445
00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:44.315
Stop crying! It's not your fault.

446
00:23:44.339 --> 00:23:47.735
You're allowed in the
women's bath until you turn 4.

447
00:23:47.759 --> 00:23:49.278
Mom.

448
00:23:49.302 --> 00:23:51.614
- Yes?
- I want to go to the men's bath...

449
00:23:51.638 --> 00:23:54.867
with my dad like other boys.

450
00:23:54.891 --> 00:23:57.927
Can you tell him to come back?

451
00:23:58.019 --> 00:23:59.122
Can you?

452
00:23:59.146 --> 00:24:01.055
Please.

453
00:24:01.731 --> 00:24:03.960
Seo-jin, come here. Stop crying.

454
00:24:03.984 --> 00:24:07.144
There, there. Is that why you're upset?

455
00:24:32.637 --> 00:24:34.380
Mom.

456
00:24:40.145 --> 00:24:41.679
Mom.

457
00:24:42.689 --> 00:24:44.390
Mom, let's go.

458
00:24:45.192 --> 00:24:46.669
What?

459
00:24:46.693 --> 00:24:48.838
- Where?
- I'm hungry.

460
00:24:48.862 --> 00:24:50.673
When I'm hungry,

461
00:24:50.697 --> 00:24:52.758
I should feed the pigs before I eat, right?

462
00:24:52.782 --> 00:24:54.317
Yes.

463
00:24:54.492 --> 00:24:56.944
- I'll be outside.
- Okay.

464
00:25:00.957 --> 00:25:04.270
Ultimately, it's better for us.

465
00:25:04.294 --> 00:25:08.539
Now that we own that cornfield,
we won't look out of place here.

466
00:25:09.925 --> 00:25:11.152
The problem is our home.

467
00:25:11.176 --> 00:25:12.835
Do you really think...

468
00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:16.339
our problem is getting a home?

469
00:25:16.765 --> 00:25:18.159
Oh, right.

470
00:25:18.183 --> 00:25:21.344
Come to your senses!

471
00:25:23.188 --> 00:25:25.681
If we don't find anything
by the end of the election,

472
00:25:25.899 --> 00:25:27.501
we're both doomed.

473
00:25:27.525 --> 00:25:29.143
Yes, sir.

474
00:25:31.321 --> 00:25:33.341
It's not in the farm.

475
00:25:33.365 --> 00:25:36.177
It must be somewhere in her home.

476
00:25:36.201 --> 00:25:39.862
Let's first find out if anybody is inside.

477
00:25:40.163 --> 00:25:41.697
Okay.

478
00:25:42.082 --> 00:25:43.699
Hey.

479
00:25:50.173 --> 00:25:53.277
A couple of guys who don't even
know the measurement unit for rice...

480
00:25:53.301 --> 00:25:55.947
suddenly turn up at a country village...

481
00:25:55.971 --> 00:25:59.200
and pay twice the price for
land, in cash, to start farming.

482
00:25:59.224 --> 00:26:00.790
There are only two reasons for that.

483
00:26:00.814 --> 00:26:03.162
One, because you're very sick.

484
00:26:03.186 --> 00:26:05.539
Two, because you're very sick.

485
00:26:05.563 --> 00:26:09.543
Or you could be running away from
trouble or planning to cause trouble.

486
00:26:09.567 --> 00:26:10.670
Excuse me.

487
00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:14.647
You said there are only two
reasons, but you listed four.

488
00:26:14.698 --> 00:26:16.175
Right.

489
00:26:16.199 --> 00:26:17.802
There must be a misunderstanding.

490
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:20.513
We just want to farm, that's all.

491
00:26:20.537 --> 00:26:22.974
Okay then. Let's do this.

492
00:26:22.998 --> 00:26:25.643
I'll help you find a home,

493
00:26:25.667 --> 00:26:27.728
and provide consulting services,

494
00:26:27.752 --> 00:26:30.189
from choosing crops to
learning farming techniques.

495
00:26:30.213 --> 00:26:32.108
- No, you don't have to...
- All right.

496
00:26:32.132 --> 00:26:35.319
In that case, why don't we discuss this...

497
00:26:35.343 --> 00:26:38.239
over a glass of <i>makgeolli?</i>

498
00:26:38.263 --> 00:26:40.908
There's a brewery nearby
that's been around for 35 years,

499
00:26:40.932 --> 00:26:42.159
and it's amazing.

500
00:26:42.183 --> 00:26:43.119
Really?

501
00:26:43.143 --> 00:26:44.620
You must like <i>makgeolli.</i>

502
00:26:44.644 --> 00:26:46.330
- Yes.
- Let's go.

503
00:26:46.354 --> 00:26:49.432
- Wait, sir. Hey!
- It's really good.

504
00:26:52.777 --> 00:26:53.879
Hey.

505
00:26:53.903 --> 00:26:57.091
Let's say one mother pig costs $300.

506
00:26:57.115 --> 00:26:58.092
Okay.

507
00:26:58.116 --> 00:26:59.510
But a buyer comes and says,

508
00:26:59.534 --> 00:27:01.679
"Goodness, sir."

509
00:27:01.703 --> 00:27:03.639
"Only summer pigs cost that much."

510
00:27:03.663 --> 00:27:06.767
"There's an increase in supply now,
so the price has dropped a lot."

511
00:27:06.791 --> 00:27:09.478
"I'll give you $250."

512
00:27:09.502 --> 00:27:10.688
What should you do?

513
00:27:10.712 --> 00:27:13.873
Hey, you thief! I'm not selling it to you!

514
00:27:14.507 --> 00:27:16.235
Yes, good job.

515
00:27:16.259 --> 00:27:19.253
- Next, the sawdust distributor.
- Okay.

516
00:27:19.554 --> 00:27:21.407
The sawdust distributor...

517
00:27:21.431 --> 00:27:25.676
wants 22 cents per kilo
when it used to be 19 cents.

518
00:27:25.769 --> 00:27:29.749
Then he says, "This was made
with red pine tree from Russia,"

519
00:27:29.773 --> 00:27:31.417
"so it's much better quality."

520
00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:34.253
"If you make compost out of
this and use it to grow potatoes,"

521
00:27:34.277 --> 00:27:36.964
"they'll grow as big as watermelons."

522
00:27:36.988 --> 00:27:38.814
Then what should you do?

523
00:27:43.870 --> 00:27:46.724
A shameless beast like you must leave!

524
00:27:46.748 --> 00:27:48.783
My goodness.

525
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:52.021
Where did you learn such words?

526
00:27:52.045 --> 00:27:53.788
Over there.

527
00:27:55.131 --> 00:27:59.431
