602
00:31:28.636 --> 00:31:32.867
Those goats have been going around
doing all kinds of goat things...

603
00:31:32.891 --> 00:31:34.952
all around the village,

604
00:31:34.976 --> 00:31:37.538
and they finally ended up causing trouble.

605
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:41.056
Goodness.

606
00:31:41.608 --> 00:31:44.476
I feel so bad for Young-soon.

607
00:31:47.906 --> 00:31:52.151
Sir, please don't. Please don't kill our pigs!

608
00:31:52.410 --> 00:31:54.138
Mom, do something.

609
00:31:54.162 --> 00:31:56.765
Stop them!

610
00:31:56.789 --> 00:31:58.392
Andrea, please.

611
00:31:58.416 --> 00:32:01.201
Andrea, do something.

612
00:32:09.344 --> 00:32:11.071
Leave her alone!

613
00:32:11.095 --> 00:32:14.006
She's feeding her piglets!

614
00:32:14.057 --> 00:32:16.342
Just leave her there.

615
00:32:36.871 --> 00:32:39.740
- Spread out.
- This way.

616
00:32:40.166 --> 00:32:42.478
Be careful.

617
00:32:42.502 --> 00:32:44.286
This way.

618
00:32:47.382 --> 00:32:49.041
Why?

619
00:32:52.595 --> 00:32:56.215
Why?!

620
00:32:59.519 --> 00:33:01.345
No.

621
00:33:01.813 --> 00:33:03.832
No!

622
00:33:03.856 --> 00:33:05.334
No!

623
00:33:05.358 --> 00:33:07.211
No!

624
00:33:07.235 --> 00:33:08.587
- Mom.
- Ms. Jin.

625
00:33:08.611 --> 00:33:10.756
- No, stop it, Mom.
- Ms. Jin.

626
00:33:10.780 --> 00:33:12.523
No, Mom.

627
00:33:12.615 --> 00:33:13.842
No.

628
00:33:13.866 --> 00:33:18.445
- You can't do this to them.
- Ms. Jin.

629
00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:22.059
They don't deserve to die like this!

630
00:33:22.083 --> 00:33:24.353
You can't do this to them!

631
00:33:24.377 --> 00:33:26.563
You can't!

632
00:33:26.587 --> 00:33:28.330
No.

633
00:33:28.756 --> 00:33:30.985
Those poor things.

634
00:33:31.009 --> 00:33:34.086
Those poor things!

635
00:33:34.137 --> 00:33:38.674
Those poor things!

636
00:33:39.142 --> 00:33:41.051
No!

637
00:33:41.227 --> 00:33:44.581
Those poor things!

638
00:33:44.605 --> 00:33:46.250
- No!
- Don't do that!

639
00:33:46.274 --> 00:33:49.837
- Those pigs aren't sick!
- Goodness.

640
00:33:49.861 --> 00:33:53.298
- I can't watch.
- I'm sorry!

641
00:33:53.322 --> 00:33:56.135
Isn't this too harsh?

642
00:33:56.159 --> 00:33:58.012
Please be reborn as humans...

643
00:33:58.036 --> 00:34:00.139
in your next life.

644
00:34:00.163 --> 00:34:03.267
- Goodness.
- Human? Life will be tougher.

645
00:34:03.291 --> 00:34:05.185
- My goodness!
- Hey, Mr. Choi.

646
00:34:05.209 --> 00:34:08.814
I'm glad you called.

647
00:34:08.838 --> 00:34:12.249
Hello. It's me, Sam-sik.

648
00:34:15.178 --> 00:34:17.254
No.

649
00:34:17.638 --> 00:34:19.324
I don't have the money yet.

650
00:34:19.348 --> 00:34:20.492
<i><font color="#ffff00">Fairy Brewery</font></i>

651
00:34:20.516 --> 00:34:23.537
But if you give me more time,

652
00:34:23.561 --> 00:34:27.332
I'll pay back $200,000 including interest.

653
00:34:27.356 --> 00:34:30.309
Just one month. I promise you.

654
00:34:32.278 --> 00:34:36.091
♫ <i>I promise, I do</i> ♫

655
00:34:36.115 --> 00:34:37.259
♫ <i>I do</i> ♫

656
00:34:37.283 --> 00:34:38.659
<i><font color="#ffff00">Fairy Brewery, Fairy Real Estate,
Fairy Fortune Telling</font></i>

657
00:34:39.952 --> 00:34:42.321
Darn it.

658
00:34:42.663 --> 00:34:45.684
Who drank my alcohol?

659
00:34:45.708 --> 00:34:47.186
I got you, you punk.

660
00:34:47.210 --> 00:34:49.646
What? It's you, Sam-sik.

661
00:34:49.670 --> 00:34:52.608
Goodness, Mr. Yang.

662
00:34:52.632 --> 00:34:55.903
Your security system is
still cutting-edge technology.

663
00:34:55.927 --> 00:34:57.613
I can never steal from your place.

664
00:34:57.637 --> 00:34:58.655
Goodness.

665
00:34:58.679 --> 00:35:01.492
I took a few bottles of
<i>makgeolli</i> to drink with my friends.

666
00:35:01.516 --> 00:35:03.619
You can put it under my dad's tab.

667
00:35:03.643 --> 00:35:06.622
Hey, tell him to pay his tab.

668
00:35:06.646 --> 00:35:08.457
- Okay.
- Hey.

669
00:35:08.481 --> 00:35:12.711
And I put aside those bottles
to use for my ritual tomorrow.

670
00:35:12.735 --> 00:35:14.379
How could you take them?

671
00:35:14.403 --> 00:35:17.007
- All right. Where were we?
- Goodness, that punk.

672
00:35:17.031 --> 00:35:19.051
Yes, farming funds.

673
00:35:19.075 --> 00:35:24.306
Call the agricultural technology
center to apply for the fund.

674
00:35:24.330 --> 00:35:26.934
- Once you call...
- And listen.

675
00:35:26.958 --> 00:35:29.728
Do you know Kang-ho's family is in big trouble?

676
00:35:29.752 --> 00:35:31.730
It's worse than big trouble.

677
00:35:31.754 --> 00:35:33.899
That genius became an idiot overnight.

678
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:34.817
You punk.

679
00:35:34.841 --> 00:35:37.736
Not Kang-ho. I'm talking about the farm.

680
00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:40.197
The poor pigs were all culled...

681
00:35:40.221 --> 00:35:44.284
because of the outbreak of
the foot-and-mouth disease.

682
00:35:44.308 --> 00:35:46.286
- What?
- <i>Foot-and-mouth disease?</i>

683
00:35:46.310 --> 00:35:48.747
They sacrificed all those pigs...

684
00:35:48.771 --> 00:35:51.557
who were squealing and struggling to survive.

685
00:35:53.651 --> 00:35:56.311
It was painful for me to watch.

686
00:35:56.612 --> 00:35:57.798
Imagine how she felt.

687
00:35:57.822 --> 00:36:00.801
She fed and raised them like they were her own.

688
00:36:00.825 --> 00:36:02.761
She must be heartbroken.

689
00:36:02.785 --> 00:36:05.055
What about Lion?

690
00:36:05.079 --> 00:36:07.224
Is Lion dead too?

691
00:36:07.248 --> 00:36:09.434
Kang-ho's home...

692
00:36:09.458 --> 00:36:12.146
is over 2 miles from the goat farm,

693
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:13.981
so Lion is still alive.

694
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:16.567
- What a relief.
- What a relief.

695
00:36:16.591 --> 00:36:18.527
What's a relief?

696
00:36:18.551 --> 00:36:20.654
This is absurd.

697
00:36:20.678 --> 00:36:22.656
Some had to die,

698
00:36:22.680 --> 00:36:25.173
while others lived...

699
00:36:25.224 --> 00:36:27.593
by a matter of a few yards.

700
00:36:27.643 --> 00:36:29.303
Goodness.

701
00:36:30.938 --> 00:36:33.682
Thankfully, this one must've survived.

702
00:36:34.609 --> 00:36:38.213
But what's the point?
She lost all the other pigs.

703
00:36:38.237 --> 00:36:40.507
She must be very shocked.

704
00:36:40.531 --> 00:36:43.483
She hasn't returned from the farm.

705
00:36:43.576 --> 00:36:45.277
Shut up.

706
00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:50.767
And start searching.

707
00:36:50.791 --> 00:36:52.326
Yes, sir.

708
00:36:55.463 --> 00:36:58.650
I don't think it's in here.

709
00:36:58.674 --> 00:37:01.919
I don't see any files. There
are just clothes and shoes.

710
00:37:04.013 --> 00:37:07.382
Look, more clothes and shoes.

711
00:37:12.313 --> 00:37:14.056
Mr. Soh.

712
00:37:22.531 --> 00:37:24.843
Thank you for coming to the family meeting...

713
00:37:24.867 --> 00:37:28.764
for our children's wedding
despite your busy schedule.

714
00:37:28.788 --> 00:37:33.018
It's to prepare my dearest
daughter and a great man like him...

715
00:37:33.042 --> 00:37:35.938
for their new journey together.

716
00:37:35.962 --> 00:37:39.831
I'd rather miss out on a campaign.

717
00:37:42.301 --> 00:37:46.990
Thank you for considering
my humble son a great man.

718
00:37:47.014 --> 00:37:48.909
I'm very grateful.

719
00:37:48.933 --> 00:37:51.370
We can tell a lot about
a person by their parents.

720
00:37:51.394 --> 00:37:53.205
Think of who you are, sir.

721
00:37:53.229 --> 00:37:56.583
You were born into a poor farm,
then later founded Dosang Group,

722
00:37:56.607 --> 00:37:59.836
the top corporation that's the
backbone of our country's economy.

723
00:37:59.860 --> 00:38:03.772
People often tease me, calling
me a rags-to-riches story.

724
00:38:05.741 --> 00:38:06.802
Sir.

725
00:38:06.826 --> 00:38:10.222
That's why I wish to become President.

726
00:38:10.246 --> 00:38:12.975
A world where one can rise from the bottom up.

727
00:38:12.999 --> 00:38:15.435
These days, social injustice seems permanent,

728
00:38:15.459 --> 00:38:17.562
and wealth and poverty are inherited.

729
00:38:17.586 --> 00:38:20.065
Therefore no one can rise from the bottom up.

730
00:38:20.089 --> 00:38:24.945
That's why the disadvantaged
don't make an effort to grow,

731
00:38:24.969 --> 00:38:28.865
and continue to just live
in this hopeless society.

732
00:38:28.889 --> 00:38:30.549
I'll...

733
00:38:31.100 --> 00:38:36.138
make Korea a place where one can rise.

734
00:38:37.356 --> 00:38:38.792
And...

735
00:38:38.816 --> 00:38:40.794
the future of my politics...

736
00:38:40.818 --> 00:38:44.104
is you, sir.

737
00:39:01.672 --> 00:39:03.373
Mom.

738
00:39:03.799 --> 00:39:06.418
We should go now.

739
00:39:10.639 --> 00:39:12.424
Yes.

740
00:39:15.811 --> 00:39:18.555
We should go.

741
00:39:19.774 --> 00:39:21.192
<i><font color="#ffff00">Ungryeol Agricultural Chemicals</font></i>

742
00:39:22.401 --> 00:39:24.129
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">When Nails Come</font></i>

743
00:39:24.153 --> 00:39:25.714
{\an8}Have you heard the news?

744
00:39:25.738 --> 00:39:27.716
About Jou-ri.

745
00:39:27.740 --> 00:39:30.001
