792
00:42:15.658 --> 00:42:19.361
also went out with the <i>gimbap</i> I made,

793
00:42:19.787 --> 00:42:22.489
and never came back.

794
00:42:23.916 --> 00:42:26.201
I was scared of that.

795
00:42:27.169 --> 00:42:29.037
That's why I never let you go.

796
00:42:30.631 --> 00:42:33.959
I was scared by the thought...

797
00:42:35.511 --> 00:42:37.587
of becoming alone again.

798
00:42:52.194 --> 00:42:54.020
Mom.

799
00:43:02.079 --> 00:43:04.030
I'll open it for you.

800
00:43:08.377 --> 00:43:12.357
In return, after we drink this,
we have to go down and eat.

801
00:43:12.381 --> 00:43:14.040
I'm hungry.

802
00:43:14.258 --> 00:43:15.986
And what do we do before we eat?

803
00:43:16.010 --> 00:43:18.461
Feed the pigs first.

804
00:43:18.721 --> 00:43:20.964
We have to feed Lion.

805
00:43:21.599 --> 00:43:22.951
Lion will grow up,

806
00:43:22.975 --> 00:43:25.161
have piglets, more piglets,

807
00:43:25.185 --> 00:43:27.178
and more.

808
00:43:27.229 --> 00:43:30.473
Then we'll be able to run
our pig farm again, right?

809
00:43:31.942 --> 00:43:34.436
I'll help you out a lot, Mom.

810
00:43:41.577 --> 00:43:42.971
Ms. Jin!

811
00:43:42.995 --> 00:43:44.904
Kang-ho!

812
00:43:44.997 --> 00:43:46.865
Are you home?

813
00:43:47.416 --> 00:43:49.185
Ms. Jin!

814
00:43:49.209 --> 00:43:51.062
Look at this. I knew it.

815
00:43:51.086 --> 00:43:53.189
You're here to see Kang-ho because
you heard about the outbreak, right?

816
00:43:53.213 --> 00:43:54.858
Have you seen Ms. Jin and Kang-ho?

817
00:43:54.882 --> 00:43:55.900
They aren't home?

818
00:43:55.924 --> 00:43:59.502
Their farm is closed off now. Where did they go?

819
00:44:00.846 --> 00:44:02.073
Ms. Jin!

820
00:44:02.097 --> 00:44:03.241
- Kang-ho!
- Hey.

821
00:44:03.265 --> 00:44:05.425
- There they are.
- What?

822
00:44:06.977 --> 00:44:09.387
Hello, Ms. Jin.

823
00:44:09.438 --> 00:44:12.265
I was worried after hearing the news.

824
00:44:12.316 --> 00:44:14.878
You must be heartbroken.

825
00:44:14.902 --> 00:44:16.403
<i><font color="#ffff00">Ungryeol Agricultural Chemicals</font></i>

826
00:44:24.036 --> 00:44:25.820
This.

827
00:44:26.455 --> 00:44:30.825
I should take the herbicide to
my mom at the garlic field, right?

828
00:44:32.002 --> 00:44:33.870
Right?

829
00:44:35.798 --> 00:44:37.457
Yes.

830
00:44:38.300 --> 00:44:40.251
Goodbye then.

831
00:44:45.432 --> 00:44:46.966
Kang-ho.

832
00:44:47.393 --> 00:44:48.370
Yes?

833
00:44:48.394 --> 00:44:51.081
Can you go to the public
bath with Seo-jin tomorrow?

834
00:44:51.105 --> 00:44:53.348
Sam-sik will go too.

835
00:44:53.774 --> 00:44:55.126
Me?

836
00:44:55.150 --> 00:44:56.544
Why would I...?

837
00:44:56.568 --> 00:44:59.005
I should go, right? Of course.

838
00:44:59.029 --> 00:45:01.257
Sounds great. I'd love to.

839
00:45:01.281 --> 00:45:04.150
Okay. See you tomorrow then.

840
00:45:05.536 --> 00:45:07.278
Goodbye, ma'am.

841
00:45:09.706 --> 00:45:12.450
I'll get going too then.

842
00:45:16.672 --> 00:45:19.040
What's going on?

843
00:45:20.426 --> 00:45:25.088
Tell me. What is it? Why do
I have to go bathe with Seo-jin?

844
00:45:28.642 --> 00:45:31.454
Wait. Are you crying?

845
00:45:31.478 --> 00:45:35.223
Something serious must be going on.

846
00:45:35.441 --> 00:45:37.058
What is it?

847
00:45:37.359 --> 00:45:38.378
Tell me now!

848
00:45:38.402 --> 00:45:40.255
Nothing's going on.

849
00:45:40.279 --> 00:45:41.840
It's just a bath.

850
00:45:41.864 --> 00:45:43.591
Everyone should bathe!

851
00:45:43.615 --> 00:45:46.192
Don't you wash up?

852
00:45:50.539 --> 00:45:51.891
I'll wash up!

853
00:45:51.915 --> 00:45:53.741
I will.

854
00:45:55.002 --> 00:45:56.146
Her son...

855
00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:58.940
must've told her he wants to bathe with his dad,

856
00:45:58.964 --> 00:46:01.109
and it must've broken her heart.

857
00:46:01.133 --> 00:46:02.485
Goodness.

858
00:46:02.509 --> 00:46:04.362
I see she was too shy to tell me,

859
00:46:04.386 --> 00:46:08.131
so she dragged that idiot in to make me go.

860
00:46:08.474 --> 00:46:09.742
At any rate,

861
00:46:09.766 --> 00:46:12.844
you were cute today, as always, Mi-joo!

862
00:46:32.039 --> 00:46:33.823
Young-soon.

863
00:46:34.291 --> 00:46:36.534
Young-soon, are you home?

864
00:46:37.836 --> 00:46:40.079
It's heartbreaking.

865
00:46:41.131 --> 00:46:43.583
What are those?

866
00:46:44.510 --> 00:46:46.029
Please take this.

867
00:46:46.053 --> 00:46:48.490
What is this?

868
00:46:48.514 --> 00:46:50.241
Wait, this is from that time.

869
00:46:50.265 --> 00:46:53.495
- You're right.
- Why are you giving these to us?

870
00:46:53.519 --> 00:46:56.095
Thanks to you two,

871
00:46:56.605 --> 00:47:00.433
I was able to get through some difficult times.

872
00:47:01.193 --> 00:47:06.231
I know this is nowhere
enough to show my gratitude,

873
00:47:06.281 --> 00:47:08.733
but please take it.

874
00:47:09.576 --> 00:47:10.762
What are you doing?

875
00:47:10.786 --> 00:47:13.139
- Are you crazy?
- You must be.

876
00:47:13.163 --> 00:47:15.642
This is wrong. Don't do this.

877
00:47:15.666 --> 00:47:17.852
I mean, Kang-ho's fiancée brought...

878
00:47:17.876 --> 00:47:19.479
Hey.

879
00:47:19.503 --> 00:47:20.730
Oh, no. Never mind.

880
00:47:20.754 --> 00:47:22.914
You're right.

881
00:47:23.549 --> 00:47:26.292
That's why I feel awful...

882
00:47:26.385 --> 00:47:28.836
whenever I see these.

883
00:47:29.805 --> 00:47:31.366
But...

884
00:47:31.390 --> 00:47:33.535
if you don't want them, I'll throw them out...

885
00:47:33.559 --> 00:47:38.221
It'd be such a waste to throw them out.

886
00:47:41.817 --> 00:47:43.002
Seo-jin! Ye-jin!

887
00:47:43.026 --> 00:47:45.770
- Kang-ho!
- Kang-ho!

888
00:47:47.239 --> 00:47:49.899
Let's go to the bath.

889
00:47:51.451 --> 00:47:54.028
Over here!

890
00:47:54.121 --> 00:47:57.225
Hey, didn't you bring any toiletries?

891
00:47:57.249 --> 00:47:58.601
They have everything there.

892
00:47:58.625 --> 00:47:59.686
What do you know...

893
00:47:59.710 --> 00:48:01.062
♫ <i>about men's baths</i> ♫

894
00:48:01.086 --> 00:48:02.745
Good grief.

895
00:48:03.005 --> 00:48:05.400
You must be the famous twins.

896
00:48:05.424 --> 00:48:06.776
Nice to meet you.

897
00:48:06.800 --> 00:48:09.153
I'll be your father...

898
00:48:09.177 --> 00:48:11.155
That hurts!

899
00:48:11.179 --> 00:48:12.865
That hurts.

900
00:48:12.889 --> 00:48:15.159
He really is in pain.

901
00:48:15.183 --> 00:48:16.244
He is.

902
00:48:16.268 --> 00:48:19.664
I don't know who he is, but he's quite a guy.

903
00:48:19.688 --> 00:48:22.417
He's my friend, Sam-sik.

904
00:48:22.441 --> 00:48:24.210
Sam-sik?

905
00:48:24.234 --> 00:48:25.795
The famous thief?

906
00:48:25.819 --> 00:48:27.046
No, let's go.

907
00:48:27.070 --> 00:48:28.840
We'll return safely.

908
00:48:28.864 --> 00:48:30.690
Okay.

909
00:48:30.782 --> 00:48:33.303
Get yourself washed up and have a good time.

910
00:48:33.327 --> 00:48:34.679
Okay.

911
00:48:34.703 --> 00:48:36.514
Okay, time to go!

912
00:48:36.538 --> 00:48:38.641
- You don't want to end up like him.
- Let's go.

913
00:48:38.665 --> 00:48:40.825
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

914
00:48:41.126 --> 00:48:43.104
- That punk.
- Sorry, Sam-sik!

915
00:48:43.128 --> 00:48:45.496
His memory must've come back.

916
00:48:46.256 --> 00:48:47.957
Goodbye.

917
00:48:48.967 --> 00:48:50.710
Wait up!

918
00:48:52.888 --> 00:48:54.907
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Certified Copy of Registry</font></i>

919
00:48:54.931 --> 00:48:58.634
My health will worsen by the day,

920
00:48:59.144 --> 00:49:02.013
and I might die any day.

921
00:49:02.105 --> 00:49:07.226
I'll only end up becoming
a burden to my unwell son.

922
00:49:07.361 --> 00:49:10.089
Have you found a rehab center for your son?

923
00:49:10.113 --> 00:49:11.856
Yes.

924
00:49:12.032 --> 00:49:17.695
The fee will be deducted from
this bank account every month.

925
00:49:18.914 --> 00:49:22.727
If my son ever returns to normal,

926
00:49:22.751 --> 00:49:25.688
please grant him the rest.

927
00:49:25.712 --> 00:49:30.792
If that never happens,

928
00:49:31.426 --> 00:49:34.712
please handle everything according to my will.

929
00:49:39.935 --> 00:49:43.581
<i>So are you saying Choi Kang-ho was the one...</i>

930
00:49:43.605 --> 00:49:45.973
<i>who's been exposing Woobyeok?</i>

931
00:49:46.650 --> 00:49:49.227
Look how pretty the wig is.

932
00:49:49.611 --> 00:49:51.839
And those shoes are so cute.

933
00:49:51.863 --> 00:49:54.273
Do these fit him?

934
00:49:54.449 --> 00:49:56.969
Why don't we just get rid of Choi Kang-ho?

935
00:49:56.993 --> 00:49:58.388
What do you mean?

936
00:49:58.412 --> 00:50:02.115
If he returns to normal,
he may pose a threat to you.

937
00:50:03.542 --> 00:50:05.326
Threat?

938
00:50:05.877 --> 00:50:07.814
Hey, look.

939
00:50:07.838 --> 00:50:11.067
Kang-ho exposed everything himself,

940
00:50:11.091 --> 00:50:13.611
then went around patching it up.

941
00:50:13.635 --> 00:50:15.154
Why do you think he did that?

942
00:50:15.178 --> 00:50:17.824
That poor kid without any connections...

943
00:50:17.848 --> 00:50:22.135
worked desperately to make some kind of a tie.

944
00:50:22.227 --> 00:50:26.040
In a wig like this, no less.

945
00:50:26.064 --> 00:50:31.227
This is what a man should be like
when he has ambition in his heart.

946
00:50:35.323 --> 00:50:37.343
Mr. Soh, you just pitched...

947
00:50:37.367 --> 00:50:41.472
a four-seam fastball.

948
00:50:41.496 --> 00:50:44.308
But something isn't right.

949
00:50:44.332 --> 00:50:46.868
Don't you think so?

950
00:50:48.170 --> 00:50:50.356
Don't bring something on me,

951
00:50:50.380 --> 00:50:52.457
but on him.

952
00:50:52.507 --> 00:50:54.500
Okay?

953
00:50:54.760 --> 00:50:56.863
<i>Kim Ju-hui reports.</i>

954
00:50:56.887 --> 00:51:00.192
{\an8}<i>Candidate Oh gave his first speech in
the most heated election battleground,</i>

955
00:51:00.216 --> 00:51:05.003
{\an8}<i>insisting he's the best candidate
who can bring about change.</i>

956
00:51:10.859 --> 00:51:13.045
Move aside. How dare you?

957
00:51:13.069 --> 00:51:16.314
Come this way.

958
00:51:16.698 --> 00:51:18.509
That's my job.

959
00:51:18.533 --> 00:51:20.151
Let me do it.

960
00:51:22.537 --> 00:51:24.947
<i>Yes, I'll keep it short.</i>

961
00:51:25.499 --> 00:51:27.727
<i>A world where one can rise from the bottom up.</i>

962
00:51:27.751 --> 00:51:30.563
<i>And rise to the very top!</i>

963
00:51:30.587 --> 00:51:31.814
<i>I, Oh Tae-soo,</i>

964
00:51:31.838 --> 00:51:35.234
- "You reek of something."
- <i>...will create that world!</i>

965
00:51:35.258 --> 00:51:36.486
- What?
- <i>I, Oh Tae-soo,</i>

966
00:51:36.510 --> 00:51:39.670
- I do? Of what?
- <i>...will make it happen!</i>

967
00:51:40.263 --> 00:51:42.381
Your hair is sparkling clean.

968
00:51:42.808 --> 00:51:44.994
- <i>I'll turn Korea into a place...</i>
- No?

969
00:51:45.018 --> 00:51:48.664
<i>...where everyone can dream!</i>

970
00:51:48.688 --> 00:51:51.000
<i>I'll do it!</i>

971
00:51:51.024 --> 00:51:52.764
- "Is it the smell of dirt,"
- <i>Thank you!</i>

972
00:51:52.788 --> 00:51:55.323
"...since you came from the bottom up?"

973
00:51:56.696 --> 00:51:59.258
<i>Thank you, everyone!</i>

974
00:51:59.282 --> 00:52:01.135
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Assemblyman Oh, "A World Where
One Can Rise From the Bottom Up"</font></i>

975
00:52:01.159 --> 00:52:03.012
<i>Please give me your trust!</i>

976
00:52:03.036 --> 00:52:05.154
<i>Give me your trust!</i>

977
00:52:05.956 --> 00:52:09.310
Ye-jin, did you have a good bath?
Seo-jin, what about you?

978
00:52:09.334 --> 00:52:10.520
It's Mom!

979
00:52:10.544 --> 00:52:12.855
- Hello, Ms. Jin.
- Seo-jin, come here.

980
00:52:12.879 --> 00:52:15.164
- Mom.
- Give me your hand.

981
00:52:15.215 --> 00:52:18.945
It must've been tough to help
both Seo-jin and Kang-ho bathe.

982
00:52:18.969 --> 00:52:21.113
No, it's no trouble at all.

983
00:52:21.137 --> 00:52:23.631
What do you know? I'm the one who helped them.

984
00:52:23.932 --> 00:52:26.759
You're right. Thank you, Sam-sik.

985
00:52:27.561 --> 00:52:31.249
Kang-ho and I have an appointment.
We'll be on our way.

986
00:52:31.273 --> 00:52:33.182
Kang-ho, say bye.

987
00:52:34.401 --> 00:52:35.977
Thanks.

988
00:52:37.612 --> 00:52:39.230
Thank you.

989
00:52:40.115 --> 00:52:42.176
Bye, Ye-jin and Seo-jin.

990
00:52:42.200 --> 00:52:45.680
Let's come together next week too!

991
00:52:45.704 --> 00:52:48.114
Okay, let's do that.

992
00:52:48.331 --> 00:52:49.642
Bye.

993
00:52:49.666 --> 00:52:51.310
- Goodbye.
- Bye!

994
00:52:51.334 --> 00:52:54.212
<i><font color="#ffff00">Geumja Public Bath</font></i>

995
00:52:58.758 --> 00:52:59.986
Guys, say goodbye.

996
00:53:00.010 --> 00:53:02.488
- Bye!
- Bye!

997
00:53:02.512 --> 00:53:04.657
- Bye!
- Bye!

998
00:53:04.681 --> 00:53:06.409
Let's come again!

999
00:53:06.433 --> 00:53:07.660
Okay!

1000
00:53:07.684 --> 00:53:09.203
- Bye!
- Bye!

1001
00:53:09.227 --> 00:53:13.014
- Bye!
- Bye!

1002
00:53:17.152 --> 00:53:20.298
Okay, the paperwork is all complete.

1003
00:53:20.322 --> 00:53:22.300
We'll take care of your son now.

1004
00:53:22.324 --> 00:53:24.552
Please don't worry.

1005
00:53:24.576 --> 00:53:28.112
It's close to your home too. Isn't this great?

1006
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:30.558
Please come by often.

1007
00:53:30.582 --> 00:53:32.366
Okay.

1008
00:53:40.508 --> 00:53:42.251
Kang-ho.

1009
00:53:43.053 --> 00:53:44.712
Yes?

1010
00:53:53.355 --> 00:53:55.264
You'll...

1011
00:53:55.607 --> 00:53:59.101
live here and be treated now.

1012
00:53:59.694 --> 00:54:02.882
There are great doctors here,

1013
00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:05.983
as well as wonderful rehabilitation equipment.

1014
00:54:06.034 --> 00:54:09.931
So they'll help you walk again...

1015
00:54:09.955 --> 00:54:12.073
very soon.

1016
00:54:18.296 --> 00:54:20.566
I have to live here now?

1017
00:54:20.590 --> 00:54:22.124
Yes.

1018
00:54:24.219 --> 00:54:26.087
With you?

1019
00:54:27.013 --> 00:54:28.756
No.

1020
00:54:29.891 --> 00:54:32.343
I can't live with you.

1021
00:54:33.061 --> 00:54:34.970
You can't?

1022
00:54:35.146 --> 00:54:36.931
Why not?

1023
00:54:37.565 --> 00:54:39.350
Because...

1024
00:54:47.701 --> 00:54:49.345
You know what?

1025
00:54:49.369 --> 00:54:52.932
If you listen to the doctors...

1026
00:54:52.956 --> 00:54:56.492
and become healthy enough to walk again,

1027
00:54:58.169 --> 00:55:01.747
I'll come back for...

1028
00:55:07.137 --> 00:55:10.506
I'll come back...

1029
00:55:12.308 --> 00:55:13.285
Mom.

1030
00:55:13.309 --> 00:55:15.136
Yes?

1031
00:55:17.063 --> 00:55:19.265
Are you going somewhere nice?

1032
00:55:20.692 --> 00:55:22.169
What?

1033
00:55:22.193 --> 00:55:23.853
Are you?

1034
00:55:26.448 --> 00:55:29.191
Are you going somewhere nice by yourself?

1035
00:55:32.912 --> 00:55:34.613
Mom...

1036
00:55:36.082 --> 00:55:38.242
Mom.

1037
00:55:39.669 --> 00:55:42.940
Mom, I'm sorry.

1038
00:55:42.964 --> 00:55:46.110
I'll never do anything bad again.

1039
00:55:46.134 --> 00:55:47.111
Mom.

1040
00:55:47.135 --> 00:55:49.155
I'll listen to everything you say,

1041
00:55:49.179 --> 00:55:50.880
and...

1042
00:55:51.056 --> 00:55:53.743
I'll stay put, I'll exercise a lot,

1043
00:55:53.767 --> 00:55:56.802
and I won't ask for a dog again.

1044
00:55:56.853 --> 00:55:59.597
Mom, please don't go.

1045
00:56:01.691 --> 00:56:04.211
Take me with you.

1046
00:56:04.235 --> 00:56:06.771
Mom, take me with you.

1047
00:56:06.905 --> 00:56:09.482
Take me with you.

1048
00:56:10.825 --> 00:56:13.611
Mom!

1049
00:56:16.748 --> 00:56:19.116
Mom.

1050
00:56:27.717 --> 00:56:29.511
<i><font color="#ffff00">Onsomang Rehabilitation Care Center</font></i>

1051
00:57:13.930 --> 00:57:15.616
<i><font color="#ffff00">Onsomang Rehabilitation Care Center</font></i>

1052
00:57:15.640 --> 00:57:18.634
<i>The phone is turned off. Your
call will be transferred to...</i>

1053
00:57:19.102 --> 00:57:21.831
She must've turned her
phone off. What should we do?

1054
00:57:21.855 --> 00:57:23.582
Why didn't you watch him?

1055
00:57:23.606 --> 00:57:26.100
